USAGE
  $ pj [options] <project_path...>

OPTIONS
  -c	generate C project directories and files
  -p	generate Python project directories and files
 
EXAMPLES
  Example 1 (C):
	$ ./pj -c /home/user/project/

  Example 2 (Python):
	$ ./pj -p /home/user/project/

STRUCTURE
  File structure generated by pj for a C project:
  
  project
  │   .gitignore
  │   Makefile
  │   README.md
  │
  └───docs
  │   │   (empty)
  │
  └───include
  │   │   exit_codes.h
  │   │   main.h
  │    
  └───src
  │   │   exit_codes.c
  │   │   main.c
  │    
  └───templates
  │   │   (empty)
  │
  └───test
      │   test.c
      │   test_all.c

  File structure generated by pj for a Python project:

  project
  │   .gitignore
  │   README.md
  │
  └───.__init__
  │   │   (empty)
  │
  └───test
      │   test.py

